---
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="description" content="About — inceptionalism.xyz" />
    <title>About — inceptionalism.xyz</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Nav />
    <main>
      <section class="intro">
        <p>
          The practice is generative art with a technical conscience. Not output — process. Each piece
          has to run when you leave the room, and run for real: real inference, real transactions, real
          compute. Authenticity here is technical, not emotional.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="selected-work">
        <h2>Selected work</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/work/confessional-booth">Confessional Booth</a></li>
          <li><a href="/work/mining-protocol">Mining Protocol</a></li>
          <li><a href="/work/valley-girls">Valley Girls</a></li>
          <li><a href="/work/1-1s">1-1s</a></li>
          <li><a href="/work/drifters">Drifters</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="statement">
        <h2>Statement</h2>
        <p>
          The work starts from a simple constraint: the piece must run when you leave the room. Not simulate
          running — actually run. The confessional booth runs real inference on real confessions. The mining
          protocol submits real shares to a real pool. Authenticity here is technical, not emotional.
        </p>
        <p>
          The recurring move is negation. Take a known object, apply boolean NOT, see what's left. The
          scarcity that critiques scarcity. The confessional that confesses to the algorithm. The portrait
          that is actually about the painter.
        </p>
        <p>
          By day I manage population health across five regions. The grid, the metric, the measured. The
          art practice exists in direct tension with that: unmeasured, autonomous, permanent. The best
          pieces are the ones where those two selves can't be told apart.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="colophon">
        <p class="muted">
          inceptionalism.xyz · rightonricky.eth · Ethereum mainnet · Foundation · Transient Labs
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  main {
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  section + section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .intro p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: #666;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .selected-work ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .selected-work a {
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .statement p {
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .statement p + p {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .colophon {
    border-top: 1px solid #e8e8e8;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
  }
</style>
